eval.reason:
The task was to visit the ArXiv Help page and find information on how to withdraw an article if the submission is not yet announced. 

The screenshots provided show navigation through the ArXiv site, including the "Submission and Revision" section, where there is a link for "Withdrawing an Article." The final screenshot displays the specific instructions for withdrawing an article before it becomes publicly available, confirming the details found in the result response. 

The response correctly summarizes: 

- You can delete or unsubmit the article to withdraw it.
- Deleting will remove it from the system, while unsubmitting will return it to an incomplete status.

This information matches what is visible in the screenshots.

Verdict: **SUCCESS**

agent_answer: I found the information on how to withdraw an article from ArXiv when the submission is not yet announced. You can delete or unsubmit the article to withdraw it. Deleting will remove it from the system, while unsubmitting will return it to an incomplete status. A withdrawal will create a new version marked as withdrawn, explaining the reason for the withdrawal and with the full text still accessible.

task.question: Visit ArXiv Help on how to withdraw an article if the submission is not yet announced.
task.answer: If your submission has not yet become publicly available you may delete or delay it. To do either of these things go to your user page and select either the Delete or Unsubmit icon.
